    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-chickpea-and-sultanastagine-with-tahini-yoghurt/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong> finely, keeping the whites and greens separate</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-chickpea-and-sultanastagine-with-tahini-yoghurt/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-chickpea-and-sultanastagine-with-tahini-yoghurt/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>sliced spring onion whites</strong>, <strong>diced pepper</strong>, <strong>baharat</strong>, <strong>harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> roasted garlic paste </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant and the pepper has softened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-chickpea-and-sultanastagine-with-tahini-yoghurt/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve <strong>half</strong> your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>in a heatproof bowl</p><p>Add your<strong> couscous </strong>and a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, then stir, cover and set aside</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-chickpea-and-sultanastagine-with-tahini-yoghurt/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong>,<strong> remaining vegetable stock mix</strong>, your<strong> diced sultanas</strong>,<strong> chopped tomatoes </strong>and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [175ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>to the pan</p><p>Cook for a further 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened and the chickpeas have warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>harissa</strong> <strong>chickpea & sultanas tagine</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-chickpea-and-sultanastagine-with-tahini-yoghurt/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the tagine is cooking, add your<strong> natural yoghurt</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>tahini</strong></p><p>Add 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>cold</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>water</strong> to loosen and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>tahini yoghurt</strong></p><p>Fluff the <strong>cooked couscous </strong>with a fork</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-chickpea-and-sultanastagine-with-tahini-yoghurt/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>harissa chickpea & sultanas tagine </strong>over the <strong>couscous</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>flaked almonds</strong>, <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>spring onion greens</strong> and<strong> tahini yoghurt</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
